<div id="review_2139117573" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2139117573" />
    <a title="Sherry" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1468288-sherry"><img alt="Sherry" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1329066951p2/1468288.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2139117573?book_show_action=true">Oct 21, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sherry" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sherry" href="/user/show/1468288-sherry">Sherry</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780984360383" href="/book/show/17240293-standing-on-the-promises-book-one">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2139117573" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16724793207053949133">finished this awhile ago but forgot to post. I really enjoyed reading about the early days of the LDS faith through the eyes of a few black saints with great faith. What courage it must have taken to join in with a bunch of sometimes rude and judgmental prople who instead of looking at the heart looked at the color. Not sure I will read the other two books but I did enjoy this one.<br/></span>

          </span>
        </div>


