  <span id="freeText13456144916393622162" style="display:none">I am so glad I read this book! It is about the first blacks that joined the church. Full of history, it really makes you think about the early church. Joseph Smith gave the priesthood to one of these early saints, and he was a seventy. Their lives weren't easy, but they were very faithful and were blessed. It made me think about the scriptures in Alma where the poor were compelled to be humble because of their circumstances. Many of these brethren and sisters were former slaves, and all of them were treated less than equals. (Except by Joseph Smith.)<br /><br />This is the first of a 3-part series, so I'll have to read the rest, of course.<br /><br /></span>
