  <span id="freeText15134378010251951172" style="display:none">Informative and enlightening. I feel a connection to these early saints and to the authors behind these historical novels. How does one stay committed to an institution that is so obviously tainted by men at times? It is unusual for me to read historical novels due to the mixture of truth with fiction, but I felt like the notes at the end of the chapter allows one to sift through such distinctions. And, in my opinion, Darius Gray gives it the authenticity it needs to be a valuable voice of Mormon history often not heard.</span>
